cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and information extraction from text.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses techniques for extracting information from large text corpora.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed system uses a joint optimization approach to learn from external knowledge bases and improve extraction quality.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with automated extraction of entities and relations from text.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of external knowledge bases as supervision for the extraction process.
